        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Ok, not sure why you are getting this information on the Rogue Pet.  I was, like you excited to get the pet.  Also like you, I was disappointed to read the stuff on the pet.  Here is my perspective as a 53 necro using the Rogue pet 90% of the time.</P><P>  I like it the pet.  With pet buff it hits fast and hits harder than the 49th pet.  It also BS's from the 150s - 160s.  I have noticed a considerable increase in damage using the Rogue pet over the 49th pet, expecially when fear kiting.  Contrary to others experiences, I have only lost two total pets because of the mob resisting fear and that was because I got like 4 resists in a row.  </P><P>  The rogue pet can take some damage and survive.  Especially with the advent of avoiding ripostes and the fix with the lifetap proc which he does alot with pet buff.  I sit in my special spot in SkyFire and pull Mature and Old Wurms and Skyfire Drakes and Bottomless devourers and Mature Chromas all day long and never have a problem.  I almost never lose the pet.  Last night, I was in OT when they did that mini GM event.  I summoned a 49th pet and commenced to killing these gm-spawned mobs.  Right away I noticed how much slower the 49th pet did damage to the mob while fear kiting those mobs.</P><P>  The rogue pet is not for ALL circumstances.  But I was overall happy with the damage upgrade.  USed properly, I like it over the 49th pet when soloing.  Better lifetap proc, higher percentage of HP healed per because of the lower hp of th epet, nice BS, generally higher dmge per hit and alot more hits.</P><P>  You will like it.  Its not the be all end all, but I think it is a very nice pet.  I guess I just don't get into situations much where the mob is breaking fear and eating the pet.  I stay close enough to gain aggro which is real easy with DoTs stacked so the pet never gets hit much.  Ohh, and their regen is very nice.</P><P>53rd Heretic of Misty Knight (Tholluxe Paels)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
